Wing—sandalled being of many hands and varied shape, housemate of man, almighty Fortune, how should thy strength and excellence be told? That which shines proudly on high, comes it but within thy ken, thou rendest privily and scatterest on the ground in a murky cloud,1 and what is mean and lowly, that, O great deity, ostentime thou dost raise alost. whether shall we call thee black Clotho or ficet-fate Necessity, or art thou Iris, the messenger 'twixt Gods and men? For thou holdest the beginning and the last end of everything that is.‘·³
